## SortedMapOpts.compare property

Key comparison function. Must follow standard comparator contract and return: - negative if `a < b` - positive if `a > b` - `0` if `a == b`

Note: The [SortedMap](./associative.sortedmap.md) implementation only uses `<` and `==` style comparisons.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
compare: Comparator<K>;
```
